title: Launch Roundup: Atlas V, Electron, and Falcon 9 missions scheduled for this week
summary: As July turns into August, launch activity will pick up after Falcon 9’s return to flight. Besides the Falcon 9, ULA’s Atlas V and Rocket Lab’s Electron are also being prepared to fly missions to orbit. The USSF-51 flight from Florida and “Owl for One, One for Owl” from New Zealand will be followed by Starlink 10-6 and CRS NG-21 aboard Falcon 9 vehicles from Florida.
